name: Clipse: Tiny Desk Concert
description:
Bobby Carter | July 11, 2025
After a 16-year hiatus and with no go-to band in place, Clipse's Tiny Desk took lots of time to piece together. At first, I didn't know exactly what they were looking for, in terms of sonics, but it clicked when I was told what they didn't want: no jazzy renditions of their music. They meant no disrespect to jazz at all, and if you follow the duo's music, it boils down to hard drums and even harder synths. Hybrid drummer Daru Jones, who played on last year's Tiny Desk for the LOX, was the first choice because of his unique ability to mix traditional and electronic drum sounds. He provided the authenticity needed for this set, and everything else fell into place.

The excitement for the Thornton brothers' return reached its apex instantly as someone in the crowd yelled "Oh my god!" at the opening note of "Virginia." There was no lull as the band coasted through "Keys Open Doors" and "Momma I'm So Sorry," from Clipse's most celebrated album, Hell Hath No Fury. I found so much to analyze witnessing the dichotomy between Pusha T and Malice up close. Malice is more collected in his movements, intensely scouring the room with his eyes while his brother is much more animated, even letting out a sinister laugh mid-set.

Recorded weeks ago, the two performed songs from their new album, Let God Sort Em Out, for the first time, including a chilling dedication to their deceased parents, "Birds Don't Sing." Before the tears from the crowd could dry, we got the moment we'd been waiting for in "Grindin'."

The first half of the year in hip-hop hasn't been the most exciting, so the timing of this reunion couldn't be better. Here's Clipse delivering its best live performance ever recorded and one of the hardest Tiny Desks of all time.

SET LIST

"Keys Open Doors"

name: 'Love Island USA': Ace Dishes On If He's The Group Leader & Confirms His HEIGHT
description: Ace Greene and Chelley Bissainthe's time on "Love Island USA" may be over, but the two already feel like winners! The pair talked to Access Hollywood after their shocking elimination and confirmed they will continue to date outside the villa. The two also shut down rumors that they were dating before they got on the show. Ace and Chelley also weighed in on if they think Nic and Olandria actually have a romantic spark and revealed if they think fellow islanders had ulterior motives when voting people out. Plus, Ace chimed in on rumors that he's the "mayor" of "Love Island" and confirmed his actual height. New episodes of "Love Island USA" stream Thursdays to Tuesdays on Peacock.

name: THE MERRY-GO-ROUND | The Amazing Digital Circus Song! ENDING A
description:
Roll up, roll up! It’s the much-requested ‘The Amazing Digital Circus’ song! A show about bunch of people trapped in a circus-themed VR game with a sinister undertone? This was inevitable really…
I’ve been a bit reluctant to do songs about animations and TV shows in the past, not just because video games are my comfortable niche, but because part of the fun is taking the world of the video game and trying to recreate it in live-action or animation. I was worried that an animation about… well, an animation, wouldn’t be particularly transformative, and might seem just like a worse version of the original media. But I hope you’ll agree that the talented team at @HibernateStudios absolutely knocked it out the park and made something that fits beautifully into the world of TADC!
You may know @HibernateStudios from their Minecraft animations for @danbull, and they also did the CG portions of Divide! for us last year. If you love this video as much I do, be sure to hop over to their channel and let them know! I’d love to work with them again soon!
Thanks to the amazing TADC voice-actors that lended their voices to our silly little project, we’re thrilled to have them! But in case it wasn’t apparent from the self-insert character, that doesn’t make this an official TADC video - just a fan project. Be sure to check out the original series on the @GLITCH Channel if you haven’t already!

Hey! my name is Moriah (pronounced muh-rye-yuh) Elizabeth and this is my channel....obviously. I'm 30 and like doing creative activities (mostly painting on things), or really anything that gives me an excuse to use rainbows, sprinkles and my own cutesy characters in excess. I'm heavy into editing, so my video are chok-full of sound effects, filters and lil....moments, or as we like to call them "MEmes." I'm not the most skilled artist out here, but I like to focus on having fun with creativity and being able to laugh at my own mistakes.
